data.title: Yep, Millie Bobby Brown & Ian Somerhalder Are Heading To Supanova Next Month
data.text:
As Supanova Comic Con & Gaming fast approaches, some names you might be familiar with have been added to the line-up.

In a last minute announcement, organisers have signed on The Vampire Diaries' Ian Somerhalder to appear at both the Melbourne and Gold Coast events and Stranger Things star Millie Bobby Brown to appear at the Melbourne event, following the cancellation of Riverdale stars Camila Mendes and Jordan Connor.

The news follows the drop of the trailer for season three of Stranger Things. If you haven't already, check it out below.

The Vampire Diaries co-star Nathaniel Buzolic (The Originals) and Steven Strait of The Expanse have also been added to the line-up.

Supanova will also celebrate the 40th anniversary of George Millerâs Mad Max franchise, with appearances from some of the original cast including Steve Bisley (Jim Goose), Hugh Keays-Byrne (Toecutter, Immortan Joe), Paul Johnstone (Cundalini), Vince Gil (Nightrider), and stuntman Dale Bensch all appearing in Melbourne.
